Recent Internal Errors: 
Computer Language: (("Determine language from source") (#(#t print mixed-fraction-e #f #t none) (default) #() "#lang racket\n" #f #t ((test) (main)) #t))
>Description:
It seems like DrRacket continues to run a program that uses places even after the stop button is pressed.

I'm not sure if this is a bug, or just a usability bug. But either way, it seems like there should be a way (in the GUI, either the stop button directly or a button right next to it) to stop all of the running places.
>How-To-Repeat:
1. In a new file, create the following program:

#lang racket

(list
 (thread
  (lambda ()
    (future (lambda ()
              (let loop () (loop))))))
 (thread
  (lambda ()
    (future (lambda ()
              (let loop () (loop))))))
 (thread
  (lambda ()
    (future (lambda ()
              (let loop () (loop))))))
 (thread
  (lambda ()
    (future (lambda ()
              (let loop () (loop)))))))

(let loop () (loop))

2. Hit run
2a. Notice in `top -o cpu` that DrRacket is now taking about 500% CPU.

3. Click stop.
3a. Not again in top that DrRacket is now at 400% cpu. I suspect this is because the main thread has stopped, but the other ones have not.
>Fix:
>Audit-Trail:
From: Leif Andersen <leif@leifandersen.net>
To: Leif Andersen <leif@leifandersen.net>, bugs@racket-lang.org
Cc: 
Subject: Re: [racket-bug] all/15207: Features continue running even after stop
 button is pressed.
Date: Thu, 24 Dec 2015 19:13:22 -0700

 Also, for whatever it's worth. When I close the tab, all of the
 running threads associated with that tab get killed. But I certainly
 should be able to do that without having to close and reopen the tab
 every time.
 
 ~Leif Andersen
 
 
