From: Robby Findler <robby@eecs.northwestern.edu>
To: Leif Andersen <leif@leifandersen.net>, bugs <bugs@racket-lang.org>
Cc: nobody <nobody@racket-lang.org>,
        bug-notification <bug-notification@racket-lang.org>
Subject: Re: [racket-bug] all/15207: Features continue running even after stop
 button is pressed.
Date: Thu, 24 Dec 2015 20:29:43 -0600

 The stop button is defined as "if I haven't been clicked recently,
 send the main thread a break. If I have, ask the user if they want me
 to shutdown the current custodian".
 
 So I think what you're seeing is the behavior that was intended.
 Perhaps you want to be doing <menukey>-k instead of clicking the stop
 button.
 
 Robby
 
 
