 > On Thu, Dec 24, 2015 at 7:29 PM, Robby Findler
 > <robby@eecs.northwestern.edu> wrote:
 >> The stop button is defined as "if I haven't been clicked recently,
 >> send the main thread a break. If I have, ask the user if they want me
 >> to shutdown the current custodian".
 >>
 >> So I think what you're seeing is the behavior that was intended.
 >> Perhaps you want to be doing <menukey>-k instead of clicking the stop
 >> button.
 >>
 >> Robby
